  "texts": [
    "We performed additional statistical analyses on the evaluation data in R. Given the small sample, we conducted Shapiro-Wilk tests to assess the normality of the distribution for each dimension.",
    "The Shapiro-Wilk tests showed significant deviations from normality, confirming our data were not normally distributed.",
    "Therefore, we opted for non-parametric tests for further analysis.",
    "A Kruskall-Wallis test showed a significant difference of means on Naturalness of errors (H(3) = 14, p = 0.002) and Retention (H(3) = 10, p = 0.02).",
    "Pairwise Mann-Whitney U comparisons with Bonferroni corrections were conducted to determine which specific models differed."
  ],
